<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 03 at 9:27AM PDT  by NWS Reno</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT WEST CENTRAL CHURCHILL COUNTY
THROUGH 1000 AM PDT...
At 927 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles west of Fallon, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fallon and Junction U.S 50 And NV 117 (sheckler Cutoff).
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
